com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.devices

Class IBeaconsRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Devices>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.devices.IBeaconsRequestExecutor

  • public class IBeaconsRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Devices>
    Request executor provided by DevicesApi. Use this class if you want to fetch iBeacon devices through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Devices iBeacons = kontaktCloud.devices().iBeacons()
      .withIds(iBeaconIDs)
      .maxResult(10)
      .execute();
